<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-784-826  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 784 826.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  August 13 1990 v4 n29 p10(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Institute helps feds combat ADP crime. (automated data processing)(the Department of Treasury's Financial Fraud Institute)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Richardson, Jennifer.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Treasury Department's Federal Law Enforcement Training Center(FLETC) established a Financial Fraud Institute (FFI) in 1989 toteach federal agents sophisticated methods of crime-busting.andP;  TheGlenco, GA, center trains law-enforcement officers from 36agencies of the basics of criminal investigations.andP;  FFI trainingis the starting point for special agents who are the vanguard offederal high-tech investigators.andP;  The Secret Service sends between50 and 100 employees per month to FFI.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Law EnforcementHigh TechnologyFraudComputer CrimesUnited States. Department of the Treasury.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>